parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or jerk while shifting gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates to shift into gear
jerks or surges forward
fails to accelerate
loses power
and may emit a whining sound. The check engine
traction control
and brake warning lights may illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to hesitate or jerk while shifting gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the torque converter can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or jerk while shifting gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates to shift into gear
jerks or surges forward
fails to accelerate
loses power
and may emit a whining sound.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash, as the airbags may not deploy properly or may deploy with excessive force.
symptoms: SRS light stays on
airbag warning light illuminates
airbags deploy without warning
airbags fail to deploy in a crash
burns or injuries from airbag deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The Takata airbag recall has been poorly managed, leading to delays, misinformation, and lack of available replacement parts, putting drivers and passengers at risk.
symptoms: Difficulty in getting recall repairs done
lack of available replacement parts
dealerships lying about recall repairs
multiple recall notices received.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt tensioner can cause injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash, as the seat belt may not properly restrain the occupant.
symptoms: Defective driver's side seat belt buckle
seat belt tensioner failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause loss of control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Power steering failure
vehicle crashes into a guardrail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The key is stuck in the ignition
the key cannot be inserted
the key turns but the vehicle does not start
the ignition switch fails to accept the key
the vehicle shuts off while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the SRS can cause the airbags to deploy unexpectedly or not deploy in the event of a crash, leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The SRS warning light is illuminated
the airbag deploys unexpectedly
the airbag does not deploy in a crash
the side airbags need to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the doors can cause injuries or fatalities, especially if the doors open or close unexpectedly while the vehicle is in motion.
symptoms: The doors do not close properly
the doors open or close unexpectedly
the doors are heavy and difficult to close
the doors do not lock or unlock properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The interior dome lights and radio fail
the fuse needs to be replaced repeatedly
the vehicle shuts off while driving.
